com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters

Class MultipleValueParser

Show UML class diagram
  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vectorprint.configuration.parameters.MultipleValueParser

  • public class MultipleValueParser
extends Object
    responsible for turning a String into an array of values of a certain type. It uses a ValueParser to yield values for the array. Used by the EnhancedMap methods that return an array of values and by Parameter.convert(java.lang.String) when the parameter type is an array. Threadsafe: it is safe to call the available parse methods from different threads at the same time on one instance of this class.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth at VectorPrint.nl
    See Also:
    MultiValueParser, MultiValueParamParser
